title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\DataTransfer\V1\DataSource
name: DataSource
description:
Defines the properties and custom parameters for a data source.

params.description: Data source client id which should be used to receive refresh token.

params.name: data.scopes
params.description: Api auth scopes for which refresh token needs to be obtained. These are scopes needed by a data source to prepare data and ingest them into BigQuery, e.g., https://www.googleapis.com/auth/bigquery

params.name: data.transfer_type
params.description: Deprecated. This field has no effect.

params.name: data.supports_multiple_transfers
params.description: Deprecated. This field has no effect.

params.name: data.update_deadline_seconds
params.description: The number of seconds to wait for an update from the data source before the Data Transfer Service marks the transfer as FAILED.

params.name: data.default_schedule
params.description: Default data transfer schedule. Examples of valid schedules include: 1st,3rd monday of month 15:30, every wed,fri of jan,jun 13:15, and first sunday of quarter 00:00.

params.name: data.supports_custom_schedule
params.description: Specifies whether the data source supports a user defined schedule, or operates on the default schedule. When set to true, user can override default schedule.

params.name: data.parameters
params.description: Data source parameters.

params.name: data.help_url
params.description: Url for the help document for this data source.

params.name: data.authorization_type
params.description: Indicates the type of authorization.

params.name: data.data_refresh_type
params.description: Specifies whether the data source supports automatic data refresh for the past few days, and how it's supported. For some data sources, data might not be complete until a few days later, so it's useful to refresh data automatically.

params.name: data.default_data_refresh_window_days
params.description: Default data refresh window on days. Only meaningful when data_refresh_type = SLIDING_WINDOW.

params.name: data.manual_runs_disabled
params.description: Disables backfilling and manual run scheduling for the data source.

params.name: data.minimum_schedule_interval
params.description: The minimum interval for scheduler to schedule runs.
